{"ProductId":"250","Title":"Bridgeport™ Steel","ShortDescription":"Timeless recessed panel style in durable, modern steel","Description":"","ThumbnailImage":null,"ShowcaseImage":"https://www.clopaydoor.com/images/default-source/product-images/showcase-images/bridgeport-595.webp?sfvrsn=22fc6bb4_12","CanonicalUrl":"https://www.clopaydoor.com/bridgeport","Overview":"<h3>Traditional, Timeless, and Built to Last</h3><h4>Flexible Construction Options</h4><p>Choose from 3-layer, 2-layer, or single-layer doors to match your needs for insulation, strength, and budget.</p><h4>Built Tough</h4><p>Durable steel construction stands up to daily use, while insulated options keep noise and weather where they belong&mdash;outside.</p><h4>Endless Style Choices</h4><p>Pick between wide or narrow recessed panels, with optional windows for extra light. Finish your door with 16 color options, including realistic <a href=\"https://www.clopaydoor.com/residential/buyingguide/ultra-grain\">Ultra-Grain&reg;</a> wood-look finishes, modern Lustra matte, or one of 1,500+ <a href=\"https://www.clopaydoor.com/residential/buyingguide/colorblast\">Color Blast&reg;</a> custom paint colors.</p><h4>Cozy and Efficient</h4><p>Insulation choices include <a href=\"https://www.clopaydoor.com/residential/buyingguide/intellicore\">Intellicore&reg; polyurethane</a> (up to 2\" thick) or energy-saving polystyrene, with R-values ranging from 6.3 to 18.4 to keep your garage comfortable in any season.</p><h4>Weather-Ready</h4><p>Add <a href=\"https://www.clopaydoor.com/buyingguide/residential/windcode-residential-information\">WindCode&reg; reinforcement</a> for extra protection in high-wind areas.</p><h4>Environmental Assurance</h4><p>Clopay doors are compliant with environmental laws and regulations. Clopay doors do not contain HFCs. All Clopay doors are compliant with:</p><ul><li>California SB 1013</li><li>Washington HB 1112 &ndash; Hydrofluorocarbon Greenhouse Gas Emissions</li><li>Canadian regulations amending the ozone-depleting substances and halocarbon alternatives regulations</li><li>New Jersey A-5583/S-3919 &ndash; Greenhouse Gas Bill</li></ul>","Options":"","Construction":"<h3>How It&rsquo;s Made: Bridgeport&trade; Steel</h3><p>The Bridgeport&trade; Steel garage door is built with your home&rsquo;s comfort and durability in mind. Choose from 1-, 2-, or 3-layer construction, each featuring heavy-duty steel inside and out. For extra comfort, select <a href=\"https://www.clopaydoor.com/residential/buyingguide/intellicore\">Intellicore&reg; polyurethane insulation</a>, Clopay&rsquo;s proprietary foam that fills every inch of the door for maximum strength, warmth, and quiet operation. Or if you want something simpler, <a href=\"https://www.clopaydoor.com/residential/buyingguide/garage-door-materials/insulation\">polystyrene insulation</a> is also available for reliable energy efficiency.</p><p>Every panel is finished with a multi-layer rust-resistant system: hot-dipped galvanizing, a protective metal oxide pretreatment, and a baked-on primer and topcoat. This means your door stands up to rain, snow, and sun, year after year, with nominal upkeep.</p><p>Other features include a replaceable vinyl bottom seal to block drafts, patented Safe-T-Bracket&reg; hardware for added safety, and removable window grilles for easy cleaning. All doors insulated with Intellicore&reg; come standard with smooth-gliding nylon rollers and heavy-duty steel hinges for lasting performance.</p><p><img src=\"https://www.clopaydoor.com/images/default-source/product-images/construction/cutaway-bridgeport-steel.webp?sfvrsn=84e68a46_7\" alt=\"Bridgeport Steel\" sf-size=\"5598\" /></p><ol><li>Steel</li><li>Intellicore&reg; Polyurethane or Polystyrene Insulation</li><li>Steel</li></ol>","Models":"","FeaturesBenefits":"","SpringsHardware":"","GroupName":"","H1HeaderTitle":"Bridgeport Steel","DisplayIndex":11,"ImageGallery":"https://www.clopaydoor.com/image-gallery/bridgeport-steel","ColorDisclaimer":"<p><strong><em></em></strong>From classic neutrals to bold statement shades, Bridgeport&trade; Steel offers a large color palette. Stick with standard White, Almond, Desert Tan, Sandtone, Bronze, Chocolate, Mocha Brown, or Charcoal, each with subtle woodgrain texture for a warm, natural appearance. Or explore premium finishes like deep Black or the richly grained Ultra-Grain&reg; Oak, available in Medium, Dark, Slate, and Walnut, with select options in low gloss for a modern twist.</p><p>If you want something more contemporary, the Lustra&trade; collection brings noteworthy matte finishes in Charcoal, Black, and Silver, or try Iron Ore for a refined look. And if you want a shade that&rsquo;s uniquely yours, the <a href=\"https://www.clopaydoor.com/residential/buyingguide/colorblast\">Color Blast&reg;</a> program lets you choose from over 1,500 custom colors.</p><p>Keep in mind: some premium and matte finishes are available only on select door models, so check which colors fit your design.</p><p>(S) Stucco Texture<br />(W) Woodgrain Texture<br />(M) Matte Texture</p><p><em>*Not available on Bridgeport Steel 1- and 2-Layer doors<br />&plusmn;Only available on Bridgeport Steel 1- and 2-layer doors<br />Premium Colors are subject to additional fee and only available on 24-gauge steel.<br />**Promotion valid on new door purchases in the Iron Ore color; savings vary by door size and location.</em></p>","TopSectionDisclaimer":"<p>Bridgeport&trade; Steel doors are available with a solid top section or you can personalize your door with a variety of window options. Choose from simple rectangular or square windows, elegant arched designs, or even add a touch of drama with decorative wrought iron styles (available in durable acrylic).</p><p>If you want a bit more privacy, you can select from plain glass or grilles in several patterns, including vertical and horizontal styles. Double car doors have exclusive &ldquo;double top&rdquo; section designs for even more curb appeal. No matter your pick, every window option is designed to complement your door&rsquo;s proportions and elevate your home&rsquo;s exterior. So, you can let the light in, show off your style, or both.</p><p><em>*Acrylic window designs.<br />Note for Double Top Sections: These are specific to double car doors, in addition to options above.</em></p>","HardwareDisclaimer":"<p>Complete your Bridgeport&trade; Steel door with hardware that&rsquo;s as sturdy as it is stylish. Every door comes standard with color-matched lift handles, blending seamlessly into your chosen finish for a polished look. But if you want to add a little extra flair, there&rsquo;s a range of decorative handle and hinge styles&mdash;spade, spear, or colonial&mdash;for you to consider.</p><p>Optional hardware is crafted from durable materials and finished to coordinate with your door, so everything feels cohesive and built to last. Add matching step plates for easy operation and an extra touch of detail. For a more distinctive look, upgrade to twisted &ldquo;T&rdquo; or &ldquo;L&rdquo; handles or select escutcheon plates for a refined finish.</p><p>These hardware options add curb appeal and bring out the best in your Bridgeport&trade; design, letting you personalize your garage door right down to the last detail.</p>","DesignDisclaimer":"<p>Depending on door height, exact door appearance and number of sections may be different than illustrations above.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://clopaypdfs.com/pdf_files/RSDR-RESISTACKGUIDE-20.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\">Click here</a>&nbsp;for complete details.</p><p>18\" sections not available on 1- and 2-layer doors.</p>","RelatedProducts":[{"Title":"Gallery<sup class='symbolstxt'>®</sup> Steel","ImageUrl":"https://www.clopaydoor.com/images/default-source/product-images/showcase-images/gallery-steel-ug-long-rec14-595.webp?sfvrsn=a7ceae04_9","Id":"12","Url":"https://www.clopaydoor.com/gallerysteel","DisplayIndex":8,"ShortDescription":"Grooved panel steel carriage house garage doors","AlternativeText":"Gallery Steel"}],"ProductBrochures":[{"Title":"Bridgeport Steel Product Brochure 3-Layer","ImageUrl":"https://www.clopaydoor.com/images/default-source/brochures/rsdr-bridgeport3layerss-20.webp?sfvrsn=97f93095_3","Type":"Brochure","Url":"https://literature.clopay.com/pdf_files/RSDR-BRIDGEPORT3LAYERSS-20.pdf","Extension":"PDF","DisplayIndex":1},{"Title":"Bridgeport Steel Product Brochure 1 & 2 Layer","ImageUrl":"https://www.clopaydoor.com/images/default-source/brochures/rsdr-bridgeport1-2layerss-22.webp?sfvrsn=c0a05706_3","Type":"Brochure","Url":"https://literature.clopay.com/pdf_files/RSDR-BRIDGEPORT1-2LAYERSS-22.pdf","Extension":"PDF","DisplayIndex":2},{"Title":"Ultra-Grain Paint Option Brochure","ImageUrl":"https://www.clopaydoor.com/images/default-source/brochures/rsdr-ultragrain-08.webp?sfvrsn=af90ad27_4","Type":"Brochure","Url":"https://literature.clopay.com/pdf_files/RSDR-ULTRAGRAIN-08.pdf","Extension":"PDF","DisplayIndex":3},{"Title":"Products Available Through Independent Dealers","ImageUrl":"https://www.clopaydoor.com/images/default-source/brochures/idea-book.webp?sfvrsn=699cfb64_5","Type":"Brochure","Url":"https://literature.clopay.com/pdf_files/RSDR-IMAGINE-14.pdf","Extension":"PDF","DisplayIndex":4}],"ProductInstallationAndCare":[{"Title":"Steel Garage Doors Care and Maintenance","ImageUrl":"https://www.clopaydoor.com/images/default-source/care-and-maintenance/steelgaragedoors.webp?sfvrsn=deb8b1e_3","Type":"Finish & Care","Url":"https://literature.clopay.com/pdf_files/CMB-4150089_EN.pdf","Extension":"PDF","DisplayIndex":1},{"Title":"Installation Manual for Residential Sectional Insulated Steel Doors","ImageUrl":"https://www.clopaydoor.com/images/default-source/installation-instructions/installmanual-insulatedresi.webp?sfvrsn=15f3a601_3","Type":"Instruction Manual","Url":"https://literature.clopay.com/pdf_files/INST-4150077_EN.pdf","Extension":"PDF","DisplayIndex":2},{"Title":"Residential Sectional 1-Layer And 2-